                            <comment id="12915766" author="rickhall" created="Tue, 28 Sep 2010 14:40:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed a patch to trunk, please close if satisfied. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12915784" author="tsen" created="Tue, 28 Sep 2010 15:26:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The code changes seem fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure about the logging strategy, since FrameworkEvents should be mapped by a logging service.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12915788" author="rickhall" created="Tue, 28 Sep 2010 15:33:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not sure what you mean by &quot;FrameworkEvents should be mapped by a logging service&quot;... If there is no logging service or no framework listeners, then failures would go unlogged. It seems reasonable to log them. The framework has no way of knowing if there is someone out there listening to events and relaying the ERROR events to anyone, so it doesn&apos;t make sense just to swallow them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
